[thinking] **Improving logging restoration**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering whether the logger gets restored correctly after setting it. If findSupportedSignal throws an error, it seems like the logger isn't restored properly. We do set previous before calling find, but we don’t set the level until we try. Maybe it would be better to improve restoration by using `Signals.unregister` in case something raises an error, and then directly restoring the logger afterward. That could help things run more smoothly!
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
